INSERT INTO public.theory_quiz_bank (course_id, question, reference_answer) VALUES
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is a classification problem? Give an example (e.g., spam detection).', 'A classification problem is a type of supervised learning where the output variable is a category or class. Example: Classifying emails as "spam" or "not spam" (binary classification).'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is a regression problem? Give an example (e.g., predicting house prices).', 'A regression problem is a type of supervised learning where the output variable is a real, continuous value. Example: Predicting the price of a house based on its features (size, location, etc.).'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is clustering? Give an example.', 'Clustering is an unsupervised learning technique that groups similar data points together based on their features. Example: Grouping customers into segments based on their purchasing history.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is association rule mining? Give a classic example (e.g., market basket analysis).', 'Association rule mining is an unsupervised learning technique used to discover interesting relationships hidden in large datasets. Classic example: Market basket analysis, discovering that customers who buy bread also often buy butter.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is a confusion matrix? Name its four components (TP, TN, FP, FN).', 'A confusion matrix is a performance measurement table for classification models. Its four components are: True Positives (TP), True Negatives (TN), False Positives (FP), and False Negatives (FN).'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Define Accuracy as a performance metric.', 'Accuracy is the ratio of correctly predicted observations to the total observations. Formula: (TP + TN) / (TP + TN + FP + FN).'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Define Precision in the context of classification.', 'Precision is the ratio of correctly predicted positive observations to the total predicted positive observations. Formula: TP / (TP + FP).'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Define Recall (Sensitivity).', 'Recall (Sensitivity) is the ratio of correctly predicted positive observations to all observations in the actual class. Formula: TP / (TP + FN).'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is the F1-score? Why is it useful?', 'The F1-score is the harmonic mean of Precision and Recall. It is useful because it provides a single score that balances both concerns, especially valuable when you have an uneven class distribution.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is an ROC curve? What does AUC represent?', 'An ROC curve is a graph showing the performance of a classification model at all classification thresholds. It plots the True Positive Rate against the False Positive Rate. AUC represents the degree of separability, telling how much the model is capable of distinguishing between classes.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Define Mean Squared Error (MSE) in the context of regression.', 'Mean Squared Error (MSE) is a common metric for regression models. It measures the average squared difference between the predicted values and the actual values. Lower values indicate a better fit.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Define R-squared. What does it tell us about a regression model?', 'R-squared (Coefficient of Determination) represents the proportion of the variance for a dependent variable that''s explained by the independent variables in a regression model. It ranges from 0 to 1, with higher values indicating a better fit.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is feature engineering? Give an example.', 'Feature engineering is the process of using domain knowledge to create new features from raw data that make machine learning algorithms work better. Example: Creating a new feature "age in days" from a "date of birth" feature.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is feature selection? Why is it important?', 'Feature selection is the process of selecting a subset of the most relevant features for use in model construction. It is important to reduce overfitting, improve accuracy, and reduce training time.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is dimensionality reduction? Name a common technique.', 'Dimensionality reduction is the process of reducing the number of random variables under consideration by obtaining a set of principal variables. A common technique is Principal Component Analysis (PCA).'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is Principal Component Analysis (PCA)?', 'PCA is a statistical technique that uses an orthogonal transformation to convert a set of observations of possibly correlated variables into a set of values of linearly uncorrelated variables called principal components. It''s used for dimensionality reduction and visualization.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is the difference between parametric and non-parametric models?', 'Parametric models assume a specific functional form and have a fixed number of parameters (e.g., linear regression). Non-parametric models do not assume a fixed form; the complexity can grow with the amount of training data (e.g., k-nearest neighbors).'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Define bias in a machine learning model.', 'Bias is the error introduced by approximating a real-world problem by a much simpler model. High bias can cause a model to miss relevant relations between features and target outputs (underfitting).'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Define variance in a machine learning model.', 'Variance is the error introduced by the model''s sensitivity to small fluctuations in the training dataset. High variance can cause a model to model the random noise in the training data (overfitting).'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Explain the bias-variance tradeoff.', 'The bias-variance tradeoff is the conflict in trying to simultaneously minimize these two sources of error. Simple models (high bias) may underfit, while complex models (high variance) may overfit. The goal is to find the optimal model complexity that minimizes total error.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is cross-validation? Briefly explain k-fold cross-validation.', 'Cross-validation is a technique for evaluating machine learning models by training several models on subsets of the available data and evaluating them on the complementary subset. K-fold divides the data into k equal-sized folds, trains on k-1 folds, and tests on the remaining fold, repeating k times.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is a hyperparameter? How is it different from a model parameter?', 'A hyperparameter is a configuration variable that is external to the model and whose value cannot be estimated from the data. It is set before training. A model parameter is an internal variable whose value is learned from the data during training (e.g., coefficients in linear regression).'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is data visualization? Why is it a crucial part of data science?', 'Data visualization is the graphical representation of information and data. It is crucial because it allows data scientists to see patterns, trends, and outliers that might not be apparent from raw numbers, and to communicate complex findings effectively.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'Name two popular programming languages used in data science.', 'Two popular programming languages are Python and R.'),
('203ee6ac-e5c8-4644-bb3c-855884ba8de4', 'What is a Jupyter Notebook? Why is it a popular tool?', 'A Jupyter Notebook is an open-source web application that allows you to create and share documents containing live code, equations, visualizations, and narrative text. It''s popular because it supports interactive, exploratory data analysis.');